Distribution and habitat. Authors have identified the habitat of this species as living on papaya trees (Pfeiffer in
Hjalmarson & Pfeiffer, 1858
; 1865 ;
Crosse, 1891
). Pfeiffer (in Hjalmarson & Pfeiffer, 1958 : 142 ) specifically reported specimens “under fallen leaves on the roots of Carica papaya , usually in pairs” (translated here from German ). However, papayas are not native to Hispaniola and other records place this species on limestone outcrops in evergreen forests. There are very few records of this species and its actual range is unknown. It is currently known only from the vicinity of Santiago de Los Caballeros in Santiago Province and from Puerto Plata and Sosúa in Puerto Plata Province.

